Column Comment.0: CLASSIFICATION: SYSTEM: Identifies and describes the classification system thatis used. The UNSPSC code set is a useful and practical source of classificationinformation.
Column Comment.1: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.2: CLASS SYSTEM DIMENSION: The type of dimension or facet that is in thistaxomony or classification system. For example, a taxonomy may exist for anorganization, or for geographic areas, or for tools and equipment or materials. Byprefrence, taxonomies should contain one dimension or as few dimensions aspossible. For classification purposes, each business object can refer to as manyclassification systems as necessary.
Column Comment.3: EFFECTIVE DATE: date on which the data in this row came into effect.
Column Comment.4: EXPIRY DATE: Date on which the data in this row of data was no longer in effect.
Column Comment.5: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.6: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.7: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.8: SOURCE DOCUMENT: Foreign key from the table that captures bibliographic orsource information. This could be a URL, book, publication or other document.
Column Comment.9: SYSTEM DEFINITION: A textual definition of this classification system.
Column Comment.10: CLASSIFICATION SYSTEM NAME: The name assigned to the classificaiton system.
Column Comment.11: CLASSIFICATION SYSTEM OWNER: the business associate who is the owner orcustodian of the classification system.
Column Comment.12: CLASSIFICATION SYSTEM REFERENCE NUMBER: A reference number assignedto a classification system, possibly by the owner. These reference numbers may notbe unique.
Column Comment.13: SYSTEM VERSION: The version number of the classification system.
Column Comment.14: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.15: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.16: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.17: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.18: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.19: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.20: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
